<wp:comment_date>2008-11-20 12:53</wp:comment_date>
<wp:comment_date_gmt>0000-00-00 00:00:00</wp:comment_date_gmt>
<wp:comment_content><div>In fact, I think employing statistics to solve problem is just like being a doctor, which required long-term traning and good memory to build up base. </div>
<div>Employing models are like using medicine, Statistical tools are like doing surgery. Both are not easy, and needs extensive time to memorize and practice. However, the most critical thing is to diagnose, to make judgement accroding to various symptoms. That's the one differentiate expert from rookie.</div></wp:comment_content>
